{
  "texts": [
    "On the effect of source blendingWith the relatively large PSF of eROSITA (see Sect. 2.2.1), source blending could become a issue in crowded regions of the sky.",
    "Empirical tests of the effect of blending (or lack thereof) on the catalog would require cross-match against X-ray catalogs where blending is expected to be negligible.",
    "Such tests, however, are potentially degenerate with source variability and non-uniformity (of background, exposure, etc.)",
    "of the matched catalogues.",
    "An alternative method is through simulations, where the full observation and detection process is simulated starting from a realistic sky source population."
  ]
}